msg

Class Message

  • java.lang.Object
    • msg.Message

  • public class Message
extends Object
    A Message is a simple container for any pertinent information needed to send information using MessagingService.

    The key field represents how the Message will be identified for transmission. Normally it will hold the destination of the Message. 

     key: Algorithms.UniversalPortfolio.ExponentiatedGradient  // sends a Message to the ExponentiatedGradient sub-algorithm of the UniversalPortfolio algorithm

    If acknowledgement of this Message is required by the sender, set the receipt flag to true. The recipient must then return the Message with the response flag set. If the recipient chooses to reject the Message, it will return the Message flagged with an error and error message. If a recipient wants to respond to a message with a String, it will return the Message flagged as a response with a response message. Use the methods accept(), reject(String), and respond(String) to complete the handling of the Message automatically.

    Author:
    Kyle
